Mapping With more Data Presentation

Zixuan Liu, Zijie Huang

11/11/2020

Introduction

  • Objective: produce US county-level maps that shows declared hurricane.
  • Source: https://www.fema.gov/openfema-data-page/public-assistance-funded-projects-details-v1.

Clean Disaster Declaration Summaries Dataset

There are total 23 variables in FEMA dataset. For our aim of the project, we filtered down to include only the hurricanes and the dates of interest. The new dataset call DisasterSummariesCleaned. The head of five observations and importnat variables are listed below:

femaDeclarationString disasterNumber incidentType paProgramDeclared designatedArea year
DR-1866-AL 1866 Hurricane 1 Baldwin (County) 2009
DR-1866-AL 1866 Hurricane 1 Mobile (County) 2009
DR-1931-TX 1931 Hurricane 1 Dawson (County) 2010
DR-1931-TX 1931 Hurricane 1 Cottle (County) 2010
DR-1931-TX 1931 Hurricane 1 Garza (County) 2010

Clean Public Assistance Funded Projects Details Dataset

There are total 22 variables in FEMA dataset, we only interested in 11 of them. We made a new dataset call hurricaneClean. The head of five observations and selected variables are listed below:
